    "name": "task",
    "purpose": "Owns the agent task runtime. task.rs defines Task { state: Arc<TaskState>, task_tx, worker }, spawns Self::run_worker(state, task_rx), exposes sender() and raise(step), privately builds model backends, starts the initial model Step with StepSignature::new(state.signature.clone(), 0, state.signature.name.clone(), StepKind::Model(ModelStepKind::Initial)) so the initial step preserves the task signature, routes task events through route_task_event, routes signed SessionEvent::Step(_, event) values through route_step_event, routes ExecutionEvent values through route_execution_event, and emits packaged SessionEvent values. Model execution is step-scoped: execute_model_step emits SessionEvent::Step(signature, StepEvent::Started/Update/Fail/Complete) using the actual step signature, sequence numbers, and accumulated StepResult content; TaskStatus::Started and TaskStatus::Canceled remain worker lifecycle statuses. task_state.rs is the plain TaskState data struct, step.rs defines the Step record, and mod.rs is namespace and re-export wiring only.",
